distraction: No; I was not doing anything else while participating in this study.  I was paying very close attention and concentrating.
strategies: Strategies?  I wasn't using any strategies that I was aware of.
familiar: I have definitely heard of most of them; but how often; or how top of mind they might be; was more the sort of thing I thought of with regard to the Familiar metric.
memorable: If a name was more top of mind for me; I rated it as memorable.  sort of vaguely; I guess; I thought some names are more bland; so to speak; not very catchy or something.
unique: There might be different interpretations of Unique.  I started with the idea of how many other cities might have the same name; because some of those names are shared by a greater or lesser amount of other cities in the US and around the world.  But sometime later in the study I began to think of unique as maybe having to do with the way a place is named; like  cities named for people; or cities with American Indian names; or cities with names that mean something that might mean the same as a different word that is the name of another city.
realistic: If I never heard of a name before; then I was less sure about how realistic it was.  I know for sure most of them are certainly real cities.  But there were a couple I wasn't sure about; so I had to try to think if it sounded like it MIGHT be the name of a city.
similar: I have never participated in a study like this one.
comments: it wasn't too boring; kind of interesting; It was a bit long.
